gn=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uladyazureskye.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LadyAzureSkye</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_magentaspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lady of the Mist</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(3/17/02 10:26:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=217.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dragon raid preferences</span><hr size=1> Most anyone, guilded, non-guilded, member of the CoG or not, are welcomed to CoG raids and events. The only exception would be for large target rules that have been set by karana guild leaders and posted on the rotation message board Karana Guild Cental (KGC).<br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub4.bravenet.com/faq/show.php?usernum=322880085&password=&catid=1023&action=showcat">pub4.bravenet.com/faq/sho...on=showcat</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br>Each raid leader also has certain rules (i.e. sign up only, late comers, etc.) that apply to the raids they run.<br><br>KCoG raids are not about loot or exp. They are about the experience of killing a dragon...clearing a plane... having fun. They often take longer to run because of the many different people and guilds involved.<br><br>If a raider is of questionable character, doesnt listen and follow the raid leadership, or other problems arise, they may be asked to leave the raid and/or not be allowed on future raids.<br><br>Lady Azure Skyeshadow<br>GL Mist Walker<br>KCoG Dragon Liason <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uladyazureskye.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LadyAzureSkye</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_magentaspot.gif" BORDER=0> at: 3/17/02 10:27:10 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukhazss.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khazss</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(3/20/02 12:53:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=217.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dragon raid preferences</span><hr size=1> All you have to do to see one of the few flaws in this method is catch up on the ever-lengthening Break Dance thread.  I was at the Naggy raid where this first came up and it was most disturbing.<br>Other than the occasional nitwit, though, I'm a big fan of this open raid concept.  Perhaps, given the interest in the raids, it would be possible for KCoG to have two slots in a few of the raid rotations?  Understandably, each one requires great effort on the part of the leaders, but again...interest...<br><br>Khazss Zraos<br>45 Shaman<br>Peacekeepers <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ueqkommisar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>eqkommisar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Can-Head</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(3/20/02 5:46:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=217.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.chrometiger.com/~anubis/stuff/canhead.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dragon raid preferences</span><hr size=1> KGC does not allow any guild or alliance to have two slots in any rotation.  As nice as that would be for a group as open as KCoG, rotations would spin way out of control if they weren'